---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site.js';
import { href } from '../lib/url.js';
---
<Base
  title="Affiliate &amp; Editorial Disclosure"
  description="How Dwellwise makes money, and the editorial policy that keeps our recommendations independent."
>
  <div class="container prose prose--page">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Home', href: href('/') }, { name: 'Disclosure', href: href('/disclosure') }]} />
    <h1>Affiliate &amp; editorial disclosure</h1>
    <p class="lead">Plain and up front: how {site.brand} makes money, and why it never changes our advice.</p>

    <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      {site.brand} is reader-supported. Many of the product links on our site are
      affiliate links, which means we may earn a small commission if you buy
      through them. This comes at <strong>no extra cost to you</strong> — the
      price is exactly the same as going direct.
    </p>
    <p>
      This income funds the site and the products we buy to test. It is what lets
      us stay independent instead of relying on manufacturers.
    </p>

    <h2>How it affects our recommendations</h2>
    <p>
      It doesn’t. We choose and rank products on merit alone. A higher commission
      never buys a higher place, we do not accept payment for a favourable
      rating, and manufacturers never see our verdicts before they publish. When
      the best product in a category has no affiliate programme, we still
      recommend it.
    </p>

    <h2>Review samples</h2>
    <p>
      We buy most of what we test. Occasionally a manufacturer lends or provides
      a sample; when they do, it comes with no conditions and earns no special
      treatment. We tell you on the page when a review is based on a supplied
      sample.
    </p>

    <h2>Accuracy</h2>
    <p>
      We work hard to keep prices, specifications and availability correct, but
      these change often. Always confirm the current details on the retailer’s
      site before you buy. If you spot an error, please tell us at
      <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
